<H2>General Information</H2>

<P>The LinuxSA Mailing List is the main method of communication
between LinuxSA members.  Linux help and general chit-chat can usually
be found here.</P>

<H2>LinuxSA Announce List</H2>

<P>The LinuxSA Announce List is a low-volume, moderated mailing list
intended for announcements relating somehow to Linux, Computing,
and/or South Australia.  Meeting announcements in particular will be
announced on this list, so if the volume of the regular list is too
great, subscribe to the announce list instead.</P>

<H2>Subscribing</H2>

<P>To subscribe to the LinuxSA Mailing List, send a message to
<A HREF="mailto:linuxsa-request@linuxsa.org.au">linuxsa-request@linuxsa.org.au</A>
with a subject of "<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">subscribe</FONT>".  The body
of the message is ignored.</P>

<P>To subscribe to the LinuxSA Announce List, send a message to
<A HREF="mailto:linuxsa-announce-request@linuxsa.org.au">linuxsa-announce-request@linuxsa.org.au</A>
with a subject of "<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">subscribe</FONT>".  The body
of the message is ignored.</P>

<P><STRONG>Please note:</STRONG> there is no need to subscribe to both
the LinuxSA Mailing List and the LinuxSA Announce List.  All postings
that are sent to linuxsa-announce@linuxsa.org.au will be forwarded to
linuxsa@linuxsa.org.au automatically (including posts that are not
approved by the moderators).</P>

<H2>Unsubscribing</H2>

<P>To unsubscribe from the LinuxSA Mailing List, send a message to
<A HREF="mailto:linuxsa-request@linuxsa.org.au">linuxsa-request@linuxsa.org.au</A>
with a subject of "<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">unsubscribe</FONT>".  The body
of the message is ignored.</P>

<P>To unsubscribe from the LinuxSA Announce List, send a message to
<A HREF="mailto:linuxsa-announce-request@linuxsa.org.au">linuxsa-announce-request@linuxsa.org.au</A>
with a subject of "<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">unsubscribe</FONT>".  The body
of the message is ignored.</P>

<H2>Posting</H2>

<P>To post to the LinuxSA mailing list, send your message to
<A HREF="mailto:linuxsa@linuxsa.org.au">linuxsa@linuxsa.org.au</A>.</P>

<H2>Important Notes</H2>

<UL>

<LI><P>Do <EM>not</EM> send subscription requests or posts from a root
account (even if you change the From line in your header).  The
listserver will ignore any requests from root and will <EM>not</EM>
bounce the message in any way.</P>

<LI><P>If more than three messages sent to your account bounce, you
will be automatically removed from the list and you will have to
resubscribe.</P>

<LI><P>Postings to the mailing list are only accepted from your
subscribed address.  This is to reduce the likelyhood of spam making
it on to the list.</P>

</UL>

<H2>Mailing list archives</H2>

<P>Archives of the mailing list are available <A
HREF="archives/thread.html">here</A>.  The archives date back to when
they started to be hosted at NetCraft Australia.</P>

